fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
Let x\xrightarrow {f} y be a map in a preabelian category. Then the
following are equivalent:

f is a monomorphism;

f has trivial kernel;

f has coimage x;

0\to  x\xrightarrow {f} y is exact.

Dually, the following are equivalent:

f is an epimorphism;

f has image y;

f has trivial cokernel;

x\xrightarrow {f} y\to  0 is exact.

It remains to show that the third implies the second. Let * be the
  terminal object. Given objects x and y, their product is constructed as
  the pullback





